(588, 1, '2015-06-27 09:09:41', '2015-06-27 02:09:41', 'The City Mini Zip is one of those strollers that gets online reviews so positive they sound too good to be true. But the raves are well deserved. The Zip folds and carries like an umbrella model, yet it has the features of a full-size standard stroller. Both the seat and canopy are made from soft, high-quality fabric. The pinch-and-pull system to recline or raise the seat is much like ones on $500-plus strollers. The Zip also handles like a much-more-expensive ride, gliding over bumps, around tight corners, and up and down curbs like a race car. Its so easy to push and steer you can do it with one hand. And then theres that fold: Push a button in the handlebar, then pull up on a strap in the seat. Pow! The stroller collapses into a compact package, easy to wrestle up stairs or into a car trunk, using the seat strap as a carrying handle.', 'Baby Jogger City Mini ZIP', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'baby-jogger-city-mini-zip', '', '', '2015-06-27 09:10:10', '2015-06-27 02:10:10', '', 0, 'http://mommee.org/?p=588', 0, 'post', '', 0),
